But Professor Charmé had no idea of what was expected of him during the following months: the catastrophic hurricane Sandy, a tax failure that some have nicknamed "Armageddon of Debt" and a growing conflict involving Israel, the place where Christian theologians of the end of time thought that the apocalypse would be triggered.
"I didn't realize it was going to be the most apocalyptic semester I've ever known," said Professor Charmé to his students at Rutgers-Camden University (New Jersey).
